    "body": "<!-- Before reporting: search existing issues and check the FAQ. -->\r\n\r\n- `nvim --version`: 0.2.0 (release)\r\n- Vim (version: ) behaves differently? N/A (no term support in Vim unless something happened while I wasn't looking)\r\n- Operating system/version: Arch Linux 14/08/2017\r\n- Terminal name/version: GNOME Terminal 3.20.2 (different host)\r\n- `$TERM`: xterm-256color\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce using `nvim -u NORC`\r\n\r\n```\r\nnvim -u NORC\r\n:set mouse=a\r\n:vsp term://bash\r\n<C-W>l\r\ni\r\n\"click in the terminal buffer with your mouse\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Actual behaviour\r\nTerminal buffer is selected and in insert mode. I often end up trying to write immediately, leading to an ocean of not modifiable errors. Exiting insert mode and reentering brings you to the proper terminal mode.\r\n\r\n### Expected behaviour\r\nTerminal buffer enters terminal mode *or* normal mode. It should never enter insert mode.\r\n",
